<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk.BlazorWebAssembly">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>
    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>
    <Version>0.6.4</Version>
    <AssemblyVersion>0.6.4.0</AssemblyVersion>
    <FileVersion>0.6.4.0</FileVersion>
    <Authors>LastOnionKnight</Authors>
    <Description>Tonberry Tactics — companion web app for the in-game plugin. AskMrRobot-style hybrid gear optimizer for FFXIV. Pure-Math by default, Balance preset queued, exports plans back to the plugin via GG-PLAN:v1: strings. v0.6.4 ("Vendored Lockstep") restores the per-job stat-priority feature that v0.6.3 tried and reverted. Three Core files (StatNames, MateriaTiers, JobPriorities) are vendored into Services/Core/ so the build is self-contained in Cloudflare Pages CI without needing a sibling checkout of the GearGoblin.Core repo. Plugin keeps its real ProjectReference unchanged; both halves agree on the GearGoblin.Core namespace and signatures. Per-job priority tables for all 21 combat jobs (plus BLU) sourced from public guides at thebalanceffxiv.com. Wire-format prefixes (GG-EXPORT:v1:, GG-PLAN:v1:) unchanged.</Description>
    <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/LastOnionKnight/TonberryTactics</RepositoryUrl>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly" Version="10.0.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.DevServer" Version="10.0.0" PrivateAssets="all" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
